-7- The return type is an implementation-defined unsigned-integer-like type.


-8- Recommended practice: The return type should be the smallest unsigned-integer-like type that
is sufficiently wide to store the product of the maximum sizes of all the underlying ranges, if such 
a type exists.


-9- Let p be the product of the sizes of all the ranges in bases_.


-10- Preconditions: p can be represented by the return type.


-11- Returns: p.



